quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  28,14,"When he reached maturity and was firmly established [in life], We gave him wisdom and knowledge. Thus do We recompense the virtuous"
  28,15,"He entered the city at a time of heedlessness among its people. And he found therein two men fighting—one from among his own faction and the other from among his enemies. Then the one from among his own faction sought his aid against the one who was from among his enemies; so Moses struck him with his fist and put an end to him. He said, “This is the work of Satan! Truly he is a manifest enemy, leading astray.”"
  28,16,"He said, “My Lord! Truly I have wronged my own soul. Forgive me.” So He forgave him. Verily He is the Forgiving, the Merciful"
  28,17,"He said, “My Lord! Because Thou hast blessed me, I shall never be a supporter of the guilty.”"
  28,18,"Morning found him in the city, fearful and vigilant, and behold, the one who had sought his help the day before cried out to him for help! Moses said to him, “Truly you are clearly in error.”"
  28,19,"But when he desired to strike him who was an enemy unto them both, he said, “O Moses! Do you desire to slay me, as you slew a soul yesterday? You desire naught but to be a tyrant on the earth, and you desire not to be among the workers of righteousness.”"
  28,20,"Then from the outskirts of the city a man came running. He said, “O Moses! Truly the notables are conspiring against you, that they might slay you. So leave! Truly I am among your sincere advisers.”"
  28,21,"So he left from there, fearful and vigilant. He said, “My Lord! Save me from the wrongdoing people!”"